com.yworks.yfiles.layout.multipage

Class MultiPageLayoutResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yworks.yfiles.layout.multipage.MultiPageLayoutResult
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IElementInfoManager

    public class MultiPageLayoutResult
extends Object
implements IElementInfoManager
    This class represents the result of a layout run of MultiPageLayout.

    A layout run subdivides the input graph into several LayoutGraphs (called page graphs) such that the layout of each graph fits the specified maximum page size. This class provides access to the different page graphs (see method getPage(int)).

    An instance of this class can be either obtained by calling MultiPageLayout.calculateLayout(LayoutGraph) or MultiPageLayout.applyLayout(LayoutGraph). In the latter case, a ILayoutCallback has to be set before starting the layout run.

      • getPage

        public LayoutGraph getPage(int pageNo)
        Returns the page graph associated with the given page number.

        A page graph is a subgraph of the input graph whose layout fits the specified maximum page size.

        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if pageNo >= pageCount or pageNo < 0
         
        A page graph contains special nodes (that are not contained in the input graph) to guarantee that no information is lost when splitting edges that connect nodes placed on different pages.
        Parameters:
        pageNo - the given page number
        Returns:
        the page graph associated with the given page number
        See Also:
        pageCount()

      • pageCount

        public int pageCount()
        Returns the number of pages available in this MultiPageLayoutResult.
